items.title: Who's in charge of Venezuela and what happens next?
items.description: Donald Trump says the US will "run" Venezuela until a "safe" transition after capturing its president and first lady.

items.title: Bowen: Trump's action could set precedent for authoritarian powers across globe
items.description: Trump seems to believe he makes the rules and others cannot have the same privileges.

items.title: Thousands stranded across Europe as Greece airspace disrupted
items.description: A fault with radio communications caused air traffic controllers to temporarily suspend arrivals and departures.

items.title: Schools to start reopening after Nigeria mass abduction
items.description: Schools in "safe and secure areas" will be allowed to reopen after 250 children were taken in November.

items.title: Police identify 16 more victims of Swiss bar fire
items.description: Among those killed by the blaze at Le Constellation is 16-year-old Swiss national Arthur Brodard, his mother confirms.
